{"id":14881834,"mediaExerciseId":"8e888daa-098a-484a-8d53-e0b86d7dabe4","exerciseName":"2","chapterName":"23","chapterTitle":"Enterprise Risk Management","groupId":612488,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":788,"solutions":[{"id":6018505,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"For this we will use the formula for profit which is given as:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\nP&=\\text{Quantity}\\times(\\text{Expiration price - Future price})\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Since we are selling five contracts, and each contract has $5000$ troy ounces, then our quantity will be:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\nQ&=5 \\times 5000\\\\\n&=25000\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"If the expiration price is $\\$17.81$, the profit will be:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\nP&=25000\\times(\\$17.81-\\$17.72)\\\\\n&=25000 \\times 0.09\\\\\n&=\\$2250.00\\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThere will be a profit of $\\$2250.00$ for this futures contract.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"If the expiration price is $\\$17.64$, the profit will be:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\nP&=25000\\times(\\$17.64-\\$17.72)\\\\\n&=25000 \\times (-0.08)\\\\\n&=\\$2000.00\\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThere will be a loss of $\\$2000.00$ for this futures contract.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"dbf5a88d-9c27-471d-be2f-fde5ed95218a","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Wes